Description: Handle sliver of pottery transport amphora. Clay fine, micaceous, grey-buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p.206,33. Trmmed. The names Sateles is attested, but only once, from Archaic Arkesine.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1728)
